EssoraFM Picom License Notice

EssoraFM Picom is a fork of yshui/picom:

    https://github.com/yshui/picom

This repository contains source code inherited from picom and additional
EssoraFM-specific integration files created for the Essora desktop.

The licensing is mixed and must be understood as follows.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Original picom source code
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The original picom source code remains licensed under the same license terms
used by the upstream picom project:

    SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0 AND MIT

The preferred license for new source files inherited from the picom project is:

    SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

The original picom project states:

    picom - a compositor for X11

    Based on xcompmgr, originally written by Keith Packard, with modifications
    from several contributors (according to the xcompmgr man page): Matthew Allum,
    Eric Anholt, Dan Doel, Thomas Luebking, Matthew Hawn, Ely Levy, Phil Blundell,
    and Carl Worth. Menu transparency was implemented by Dana Jansens.

    Numerous contributions to picom from Richard Grenville.

    See the CONTRIBUTORS file for a complete list of contributors.

    This source code is provided under:

        SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0 AND MIT

    And the preferred license for new source files in this project is:

        SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

    You can find the text of the licenses in the LICENSES directory.

All original copyright notices, authorship information, license identifiers
and contributor information from upstream picom must be preserved.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. EssoraFM-specific integration files
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

EssoraFM-specific integration files are licensed under:

    SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0-or-later

This applies to files created specifically for the EssoraFM integration,
including but not limited to:

    essora/assets/essora-picom.svg
    defaults/essorafm-picom.conf
    packaging/build-essorafm-picom-deb.sh
    EssoraFM-specific installation helpers
    EssoraFM-specific GUI helpers
    EssoraFM-specific packaging files
    EssoraFM-specific documentation files

Unless a file explicitly states a different license, EssoraFM-specific files
are licensed under the GNU General Public License version 3 or later.

Copyright:

